Enum Pass.PassingMode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Pass.PassingMode>
      • com.bmd.jrt.annotation.Pass.PassingMode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Pass.PassingMode>
    Enclosing class:
    Pass

    public static enum Pass.PassingMode
extends Enum<Pass.PassingMode>
    Asynchronous passing mode.
    The type indicates in which way a parameter is passed to the wrapped method or the result is passed outside.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      AUTO
      Automatic mode.
      The mode is automatically assigned based on the parameter or return type.
      COLLECTION
      Collection mode.
      The inputs are collected from the channel and passed as an array or collection to the wrapped method.
      OBJECT
      Object mode.
      The variable is just read from or passed to an output channel.
      PARALLEL
      Parallel mode.
      Each input is passed to a different parallel invocation of the wrapped method.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • OBJECT

        public static final Pass.PassingMode OBJECT
        Object mode.
        The variable is just read from or passed to an output channel.

        The annotated parameter must extends an OutputChannel, while an annotated method must return a super class of it.

      • COLLECTION

        public static final Pass.PassingMode COLLECTION
        Collection mode.
        The inputs are collected from the channel and passed as an array or collection to the wrapped method. In a dual way, the element of the result array or collection are passed one by one to the output channel.

        The annotated parameter must extends an OutputChannel and must be the only parameter accepted by the method, while an annotated method must return a super class of it.

      • PARALLEL

        public static final Pass.PassingMode PARALLEL
        Parallel mode.
        Each input is passed to a different parallel invocation of the wrapped method.

        The annotated parameter must be an array or implement an Iterable and must be the only parameter accepted by the method, while an annotated method must return an array or a super class of a List.

      • AUTO

        public static final Pass.PassingMode AUTO
        Automatic mode.
        The mode is automatically assigned based on the parameter or return type. Namely: if the parameters match the COLLECTION async mode, they are assigned it; if they match the OBJECT mode, they are assigned the latter; finally the PARALLEL conditions are checked.

        Dually, if the return type matches the PARALLEL async mode, it is assigned it; if it matches the COLLECTION mode, it is assigned the latter; finally the OBJECT conditions are checked.
